3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper leverages machine learning methods for optimization under uncertainty, which falls under the umbrella of AI. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The case studies presented in the paper are related to process network design and planning, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of social and information networks.
